IV- Flowering stage : 50-55 DAS

3.	Active tillering stage: 35-40 DAS
4.	Flowering stage: 50-55 DAS

Recommended for the crop requires 4 - 6 irrigations depending on the soil type and rainfall. Wheat crop requires minimum of 5 irrigations at the following critical stages.
I – Immediately after sowing
II – Crown root initiation: 15-20 DAS 
III- Active tillering stage: 35-40 DAS
IV- Flowering stage: 50-55 DAS
V- Grain filling stage: 70-75 DAS
Crown root initiation and flowering are the most critical stages. Water stagnation should be voided at the time of germination.

III- Active tillering stage : 35-40 DAS
IV- Flowering stage : 50-55 DAS
V- Grain filling stage : 70-75 DAS
Crown root initiation and flowering are the most critical stages. Water stagnation should be voided at the time of germination.

Method for Preperation of bordex pest 
1. Dissolve one kilogram of copper sulphate in 5 liter of water in plastic bucket.
2. Dissolve one kilogram of quick lime in 5 liter of water seperately in plastic bucket.
3. Both solution are mixed in one bucket same time.
4. If the prepare mixture is in acidic range, it can be brought to neutral or near alkaline condition by adding some more lime solution into the mixture. 
5. To test the neutrality of the mixture, dip a well polished knife or a sickle in the mixture for few minutes. If reddish deposit appears on the knife/sickle, it indicates the acidic nature of the mixture.

KCCAns:
Method for Preperation of bordex pest 
1. Dissolve one kilogram of copper sulphate in 5 liter of water in plastic bucket.
2. Dissolve one kilogram of quick lime in 5 liter of water seperately in plastic bucket.
3. Both solution are mixed in one bucket same time.
4. If the prepare mixture is in acidic range, it can be brought to neutral or near alkaline condition by adding some more lime solution into the mixture. 
5. To test the neutrality of the mixture, dip a well polished knife or a sickle in the mixture for few minutes. If reddish deposit appears on the knife/sickle, it indicates the acidic nature of the mixture.

KCCAns:
Vermi Compost

Friend of earthworm farmers and the intestines of land are called. These concentrated substances spread humus and soil and spread them to other layers inside the ground. With this the ground is polar and the air traffic increases and the increase in storage capacity is increased. The action of chemical action and microbes in the stomach of earthworms increases the availability of nitrogen, phosphor and potash and other subtle elements found in the soil. Vermi compost does not contain stench and flies and mosquitoes do not grow and the atmosphere is not polluted. By controlling the temperature, the bacteria are active and active. Vermi compost gets ready within one and a half months. It contains 2.5 to 3% nitrogen, 1.5 to 2% phosphor and 1.5 to 2% potash.

Preparation Method:

The fertilizer is to be made from the waste, from which the pieces of glass and metal pieces are separated properly and after this, the platform of 10x4 feet is prepared to prepare the Vermi compost up to 6 to 12 inches high. 2 ridges are added to this platform and huts are made for shade above the platform. Dry fodder on the platform, fertilize 3-4 quintals of cow dung and 7-8 quintals of garbage (Garvage) Which gets irrigated by sapling for 10-15 days so that the temperature of the compost can be reduced. After this, 100 thousand square feet are left to the extent of 10 thousand earthworms. After leaving the ketchu, the stitches are covered with jute sacks, and they keep irrigation for 4 days so that 45-50 percent moisture is maintained. Keep in mind that due to excessive wetness the air will be blocked and the microbes and earthworms will not be able to die or work.

After 45 days irrigation is stopped and jute bags are removed. After removing the brood, the top manure dries up and the earthworms go into humidity below. Then dry up

Up to 200% of the yield on the first group of April in Kerala is found. In the same irrigation areas, the highest yield of wuvai was obtained from seeding in mid-February and an 80% increase in the time of tubers was reported. Panchagavya- Panchagavya, an organic product has the potential to play the role of promoting growth and providing immunity in plant system. Panchagavya consists of nine products viz. cow dung, cow urine, milk, curd, jaggery, ghee, banana, Tender coconut and water. When suitably mixed and used, these have miraculous effects.
Cow dung - 7 kg, Cow ghee - 1 kg
Mix the above two ingredients thoroughly both in morning and evening hours and keep it for 3 days
Cow Urine - 10 liters, Water - 10 liters
After 3 days mix cow urine and water and keep it for 15 days with regular mixing both in morning and evening hours. After 15 days mix the following and panchagavya will be ready after 30 days.
Cow milk - 3 liters, Cow curd - 2 liters, Tender coconut water - 3 liters, Jaggery - 3 kg

Method for Preperation of bordex pest 
1. Dissolve one kilogram of copper sulphate in 5 liter of water in plastic bucket.
2. Dissolve one kilogram of quick lime in 5 liter of water seperately in plastic bucket.
3. Both solution are mixed in one bucket same time.
4. If the prepare mixture is in acidic range, it can be brought to neutral or near alkaline condition by adding some more lime solution into the mixture. 
5. To test the neutrality of the mixture, dip a well polished knife or a sickle in the mixture for few minutes. If reddish deposit appears on the knife/sickle, it indicates the acidic nature of the mixture.

Preparation of land:

The successful production of onions is of particular importance in the preparation of land. The first cultivation of the farm should be done with soil reversal solution. After this, do the 2 to 3 plowing cultivators or harra, after each plantation, make sure that the moisture is safe and the soil becomes brownish. The ground is 15 cm from the surface. The plantation is planted on the height of 1.2 meters on the verdant bar so that the farm should be prepared with a fixed-bed system.

Manure and fertilizer:

The onion crop requires high amounts of nutrients; fertilizers and fertilizers should be used on the basis of soil testing on the onion crop. Manure of cow dung should be planted 20-25 t / ha in the farm before one or two months before planting. In addition, nitrogen is 100 kg Per hectare, phosphor 50 kg Per hectare and potash 50 kg Recommendations are given per hectare. In addition, sulfur 25 kg and zinc 5 kg. Per hectare is necessary to improve onion quality

Seed Treatment
(A) Advantage of seed treatment- Increasing the germination capacity of seeds and protecting against seed borne tropical diseases.

(C) Method of drug use - Soak the seeds first with the sticky substances and add the medication then dry them in the shade and bowl them after 2 hours.
Use of Organic Fertilizers

(A) Benefits of using organic fertilizers - They work to provide nutrients to plants.

Method for Preperation of bordex pest 
1. Dissolve one kilogram of copper sulphate in 5 liter of water in plastic bucket.
2. Dissolve one kilogram of quick lime in 5 liter of water seperately in plastic bucket.
3. Both solution are mixed in one bucket same time.
4. If the prepare mixture is in acidic range, it can be brought to neutral or near alkaline condition by adding some more lime solution into the mixture. 
5. To test the neutrality of the mixture, dip a well polished knife or a sickle in the mixture for few minutes. If reddish deposit appears on the knife/sickle, it indicates the acidic nature of the mixture.

Method for Preperation of bordex pest 
1. Dissolve one kilogram of copper sulphate in 5 liter of water in plastic bucket.
2. Dissolve one kilogram of quick lime in 5 liter of water seperately in plastic bucket.
3. Both solution are mixed in one bucket same time.
4. If the prepare mixture is in acidic range, it can be brought to neutral or near alkaline condition by adding some more lime solution into the mixture. 
5. To test the neutrality of the mixture, dip a well polished knife or a sickle in the mixture for few minutes. If reddish deposit appears on the knife/sickle, it indicates the acidic nature of the mixture.

Seeds & Sowing -

Healthy and large sized tubes (buds) are used for sowing of garlic. Seeds are 5-6 quintals / ha. Direct buds in the middle of Shalakand should not be used for sowing. Sowing pre-buds should be treated with a solution of the combination of MacGebb + Carbendizam 3 gm drug. Garlic is sown in the trash, sprinkler or debugging method. Buds 5-7 cm Should be covered in deep depth and covered with mild soil. At the time of planting, keep the thin part of the buds above. At the time of sowing, the distance of buds from the buds is 8 cm. And the distance of the queues is 15 cm. Garlic planter can also be used for crop seeding in large areas.

KCCAns:
To prepare the compost from the waste, the pieces of glass and metal pieces are separated properly and after this, a 10x4 ft platform is prepared to prepare the Vermi Compost up to 6 to 12 inches high. Two rubbish bricks are added above this platform and huts are made for shade above the platform. Dry fodder on the platform, manure 3-4 quintals of cow dung and 7-8 quintals of garbage (Garvage) Which gets irrigated by sapling for 10-15 days so that the temperature of the compost can be reduced. After this, 100 thousand square feet are left to the extent of 10 thousand earthworms. After leaving the ketchu, the stitches are covered with jute sacks, and they keep irrigation for 4 days so that 45-50 percent moisture is maintained. Keep in mind that due to excessive wetness the air will be blocked and the microbes and earthworms will not be able to die or work.

After 45 days irrigation is stopped and jute bags are removed. After removing the brood, the top manure dries and the earthworms go down in humidity. Then separate the dry Vermic compost of the above. After 4-5 days, the upper manure of the stitches is dried and the dry manure is separated from the top. Thus, the entire compost separates from the stitches in 3-4 times and the earthworms are left in the last, whose number In two months, the number of earthworms inserted is doubled, keep in mind that do not use gantry, spade or cranberries to remove manure from hand. The manure taken from the strains is dried in a shade and filtered in a shady place. The quantity of Vermi compost requires 100 grams, one kilogram of one year plants and 6-8 quintals per acre in the crop. 2- Remove debris, debris etc. from the upper surface on the selected places.

3- 15 cm at all these places (6-9 inch) dig deeper V shaped cord. Cleansing the pot from the top of the scalp, up to 2 cm from the top. Remove the thick soil from the bottom and put it in a clean bucket or tray.

4- Mix the collected clay well with hand and make a round pile by putting it on clean clothes. Remove the clay from finger to four equal parts and remove the soil separately. Now mix the remaining two parts again and make the rounds. Repeat this procedure until almost half of the remains are left in the soil. This representative will be sample.

5- Keep the dry soil sample in a clean plastic bag and put it in a garment bag. Insert a notice sheet with a sample on which all the information is written, inside a plastic bag and outside a garment bag.

6- Now send these prepared samples to the soil testing laboratory.
